path.name: Path
path.help: A local path on the server.

url.name: Path or URL
url.help:
URL of the model repo or local path on the server.
If needed, the model will be downloaded to the cache directory and quantized.
This location may also refer to model weights that have already been quantized.

passkey.name: Password, API Key, or Access Token

resource.help: The resource tag is for code, documents, media, and other assets that can be shared or composed.

hf_token.name: HF API Token
help:
Your $HF_TOKEN or API key used for access to gated models on HuggingFace Hub.
This is only needed if you are downloading a private model or under access control.
For example, original 16-bit Llama weights. Quants do not typically need login.

CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES.name: CUDA Devices
help:
A comma-separated list of the GPU device indexes or UUIDs to enable.
This is the CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES environment variable and --gpus option in Docker.
For Jetson or other single-GPU systems, this should remain set to 0, which indicates the first detected GPU.
Clearing thie field with a blank input will result in container being run without CUDA enabled.

quantization.name: Quantization API
quantization.help: The inference API and type of quantization used.

api.name: Runtime API
api.help: The runtime library or container to use for inferencing.

max_batch_size.name: Max Batch Size
max_batch_size.help: The maximum number of generation requests to handle in parallel at one time.

max_context_len.name: Max Context Len
help: The maximum number of tokens in the chat history, including any system instruction, prompt, and future reply.
Reduce this from the model's default to decrease memory usage. This can be left unset, and the model's default will be used.

prefill_chunk.name: Prefill Chunk Len
help: The maximum number of input tokens that can be prefilled into the KV cache at once.

Longer prompts are prefilled in multiple batches.
Reduce this from the model's default to decrease memory usage.

chat_template.name: Chat Template
help: Manually set the model's conversation template.  Normally this will be attempted to be determined automatically,
but in some cases needs set and is specific to runtime APIs and model types.

tensor_parallel.name: Tensor Parallel
tensor_parallel.help: The number of GPUs to split the model across (for multi-GPU systems)
